{
  "text": "The presence of sPPases in higher plants has been documented [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , but the enzymes remain poorly characterized. Although all of these sPPases are quite active and generally comprise as much as 0.1-0.5 % of total cell protein, cytosolic PP i concentrations in photosynthetic plant tissues are maintained at millimolar levels (0.2-0.5 mM), clearly higher than those in yeast (2-5 \u00b5M) , suggesting that these enzymes may be either compartmentalized or strongly regulated. This also suggests that PP i could have an important role as an energy donor in plant metabolism [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
